snippet.textDisplay:
Since you come from movies and not comics or animation, you might want to look at the DC animation series on right now, Harley Quinn. It is a streaming DC show (13 episode 1st season) so the creators have 6.5 hours to work with, but after the first 11 episodes the writing is clever - mixing comedy, drama and action along with the message about what messes up relationships. It is like a R rated follow up of the BTAs world mixed with The Venture Brothers and Rick & Morty.


It can be very niche with deep calls into the DC comic world (all of the characters, even the minor ones are all from the comic) and sends up the whole super hero / super villain story lines. Finally it addresses the same question about the nature of being bad and being evil.
snippet.textOriginal:
Since you come from movies and not comics or animation, you might want to look at the DC animation series on right now, Harley Quinn. It is a streaming DC show (13 episode 1st season) so the creators have 6.5 hours to work with, but after the first 11 episodes the writing is clever - mixing comedy, drama and action along with the message about what messes up relationships. It is like a R rated follow up of the BTAs world mixed with The Venture Brothers and Rick & Morty.


It can be very niche with deep calls into the DC comic world (all of the characters, even the minor ones are all from the comic) and sends up the whole super hero / super villain story lines. Finally it addresses the same question about the nature of being bad and being evil.

snippet.textDisplay:
I really like the insite you give when comparing the reception for Joker and Harley. To riff off that, perhaps this could stem from Harley's 'anti-hero' status and Joker's down right 'villain' status. She's absolutely a horrible person, and in interviews Margot has said she would push back when Yan was taken away with making Harley too sympathetic. But due to her history, Harley does become sympathetic, even though she is a murderer. Meanwhile, anything sympathetic about the Joker from the movie is marked questionable due to highly unreliable narration.
Again, love that you brought this up. Its a fascinating thought!

snippet.textDisplay: I’d disagree with his score because he’s focusing too much on the pacing and downplays the characters overall. The characters are very fun throughout the whole movie. Siones’ problems with his family could’ve been better fleshed out along with dinah, but the other characters are given purpose and drive to their actions. The comedy hits most of the time with there being some low points along with those high points. I will agree the beginning of the movie has sub-par pacing and kind of takes you out of it until the second and third act hits. The plot is also basic which is a downside but it’s not bad necessarily just basic. That being said we are given great actions, good team chemistry, over the top dialogue, acceptable humor, and overall a fun atmosphere. Is it perfect? No not at all. Is it a C+? I don’t believe so it seems more like a solid B rating movie. It has issues but none of them are glaring enough to bring it down to a B. Just my opinion I enjoyed the video nonetheless
